==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Macassar oil
<hw>Ma*cas`sar oil"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of oil
formerly used in dressing the hair; -- so called because originally
obtained from <etsep>Macassar</etsep>, a district of the Island of
Celebes. Also, an imitation of the same, of perfumed castor oil and
olive oil. Cf. <er>antimacassar</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Macau</ent>⟦br⟧
